250 g Ground Beef
2 unit(s) Artisan Bun
½ cup Cheese Curds
2 tbsp Mayonnaise
⅓ cup Panko Breadcrumbs
300 g Yellow Potato
10 g Montreal Spice Blend
28 g Arugula and Spinach Mix
28 g Crispy Shallots
1 unit(s) Campbell's Cream of Mushroom Condensed Soup
1 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.06 tsp Pepper*
½ cup Milk*

Before starting, preheat the oven to 425°F.
Wash and dry all produce.
Remove any brown spots from potatoes and cut into 1/2-inch wedges.
To a parchment-lined baking sheet, add potatoes and 1 tbsp oil. (NOTE: For 4 servings, use 2 baking sheets, with 1 tbsp oil per sheet.) Season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat.
Roast in the middle of the oven for 25-28 min, flipping halfway through, until tender and golden. (NOTE: For 4 servings, roast in the middle and bottom of the oven, rotating sheets halfway through.)

In a medium bowl, combine beef, breadcrumbs, 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) Campbell's Cream of Mushroom Soup and Montreal Spice Blend. Form mixture into two (four) 4-inch wide patties.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium.
When hot, add patties to the dry pan. (NOTE: Don't crowd the pan; cook patties in 2 batches if needed.)
Pan-fry for 4-5 min per side, until cooked through.**

To a small pot, add remaining Campbell's Cream of Mushroom Soup and 1/2 cup (1 cup) milk.
Heat over medium for 5-6 min, stirring constantly, until warmed through.

Halve buns.
Directly on the top rack of the oven, arrange buns, cut-side up. Toast for 3-4 min, until browned. (TIP: Keep an eye on them so they don't burn!)

Spread mayo over top buns. Stack arugula and spinach mix and patties on bottom buns. Close with top buns.
Divide burgers and potato wedges between plates.
Top wedges with cheese curds, Campbell's Cream of Mushroom Soup and crispy shallots.